I wasn't comfortable with White's superior center, so I thought my best chance of containing the center is to challenge it, which goes into a type of French structure

Now this is sort of like a French Advance (e4 e6 d4 d5 e5 c5 c3), but there are a lot of differences.
I was able to develop my kingside knight, unlike in French Advance where it is blocked by e5. I have a pawn on b6 instead of a queen, which strengthens my center. White has undeveloped his bishop, which is dubious in this type of opening. Because of these differences, I would prefer my position.
